excerpt: Tours of local ethnic communities' traditional homes, with culinary, craft & dance demonstrations.
detail_description: Mari Mari Cultural Village offers an immersive experience into the traditional lifestyles and customs of Borneo's indigenous communities. Visitors can explore authentic homes of five ethnic groups, including the Kadazan-Dusun, Rungus, Lundayeh, Bajau, and Murut. The village provides cultural performances, demonstrations on activities like blowpipe-making and rice wine processing, as well as opportunities to try local crafts and traditional dishes.
name: Mari Mari Cultural Village
address: Jalan Kionsom, Inanam, 88450 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: This beach with a long strip of sand & food stalls is a popular place to watch the sunset.
detail_description: Tanjung Aru Beach is a must-visit destination in Kota Kinabalu, offering a picturesque setting with its long stretch of sandy shores and vibrant food stalls. It's renowned for being an ideal spot to witness breathtaking sunsets. The beach provides a refreshing change of scenery, inviting visitors to swim in its crystal-clear waters and partake in various water sports and activities. Additionally, the area boasts numerous cafes and restaurants where you can savor delicious local cuisine.
name: Tanjung Aru Beach
address: Tanjung Aru Beach Resort, Tanjung Aru, 88100 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Bustling outdoor market featuring vendors selling produce, cooked food, local crafts & souvenirs.
detail_description: Gaya Street Sunday Market, formerly known as Bond Street, has become a vibrant and popular spot for locals and tourists. Every Sunday morning, the historical area turns into a bustling market offering a wide variety of goods such as arts and crafts, batik sarongs, fresh produce, local delicacies, antiques, souvenirs, pets and herbs. The market is filled with vendors selling everything from produce to cooked food to local crafts and souvenirs.
name: Gaya Street Market
address: Gaya Street, Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Zoo housing tigers, monkeys & pygmy elephants & offering a jungle garden with a walking trail.
detail_description: Lok Kawi Wildlife Park, situated near Kota Kinabalu, is a top destination for wildlife enthusiasts. The park, established in 2007 by the Sabah Wildlife Department, features a diverse range of Borneo's exotic animals such as tigers, bears, elephants, proboscis monkeys and more. Divided into botanical and zoological sections, it aims to be family-friendly with a focus on the Children's Zoo.
name: Lok Kawi Wildlife Park
address: Lok kawi Putatan, 88200 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Visitors can climb stairs to reach the top of this landmark with snack shops & panoramic views.
detail_description: Signal Hill Observatory Tower is a must-visit destination for anyone exploring Kota Kinabalu. This iconic landmark offers visitors the chance to ascend its stairs and soak in breathtaking panoramic views of the city, Gaya Bay, and the stunning islands of Tunku Abdul Rahman Marine Park. Although renovations are underway at the observatory platform until September 2023, adventurers can still trek to various vantage points around the hilltop for spectacular sights.
name: Signal Hill Observatory Tower
address: 78, Jalan Asrama, signal hills, 88400 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: State museum with an art gallery & exhibits on topics such as archeology & Islamic civilization.
detail_description: The Sabah State Museum, also known as Muzium Sabah, has come a long way since its establishment in 1965. It is now located on a 17-hectare land at Bukit Istana Lama and houses an extensive collection of artifacts, installations, and exhibits in various galleries covering history, arts, ceramics, brassware, natural history, archaeology, ethnography, and Islamic civilization.
name: Sabah State Museum (Muzium Sabah)
address: sabah museum complex, Jalan Muzium, 88300 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Sabah's oldest structure, a 1905 wooden clocktower named after a British colonial administrator.
detail_description: Atkinson Clock Tower, also known as Menara Jam Atkinson, is a historic wooden clock tower in Kota Kinabalu, Sabah. Built in 1905 to commemorate Francis George Atkinson, a British colonial administrator who passed away at the age of 28 due to malaria, it stands at 15.7 meters tall and is one of the oldest structures in Sabah. The tower was funded by Atkinson's family and sailors' contributions.
name: Atkinson Clock Tower
address: Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Waterfront market specializing in seafood, plus street food stalls, jewelry, handicrafts & clothing.
detail_description: The Handicraft Market, also known as the Filipino Market, is a vibrant waterfront market in Kota Kinabalu. It offers a wide range of items including jewelry, clothing, and handicrafts from various parts of Asia. Visitors can find unique souvenirs such as pearl jewelry, textiles, seashell crafts, and bamboo goods. The market is also a great place to sample local street food with a focus on seafood.
name: Handicraft Market
address: Jalan Tun Fuad Stephen, Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Completed in 1975, this contemporary mosque in the city's center can accommodate 5,000 visitors.
detail_description: The Sabah State Mosque, completed in 1975, is a grand symbol of Islamic architecture in the heart of Kota Kinabalu. With a capacity for 5,000 visitors, it stands as a testament to the Muslim faith in Sabah. Inspired by iconic mosques like Al Aqsa and the Blue Mosque, its design includes a towering 215-foot minaret reminiscent of Mecca and Medina.
name: Sabah State Mosque
address: Jln Tunku Abdul Rahman, 88100 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Monsopiad Heritage Village, located near the Penampang River in Sabah, offers a captivating insight into the traditional lifestyle of the Kadazan-Dusun people. This living museum showcases authentic homes, gardens, and cultural performances that provide visitors with a deep understanding of this indigenous community's customs and traditions. By preserving the vanishing heritage of these ancient head-hunters, Monsopiad Heritage Village plays a vital role in educating and enlightening others about this rich cultural legacy.
name: Monsopiad Heritage Village
address: Kampung Kuai Kandazon, Jalan Putatan Ramayah, 89507 Penampang, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Kota Kinabalu is the capital of Malaysia’s Sabah state in the northern part of the island of Borneo. Often referred to as KK, it’s a coastal city partly surrounded by rainforest. It's known for its bustling markets, modern boardwalk, beaches and waterfront Kota Kinabalu City Mosque. It is also a gateway to Kinabalu National Park, the home of 4,095m-high Mount Kinabalu.
detail_description: Kota Kinabalu, also known as KK, is the capital of Sabah in Malaysia and is located on the island of Borneo. This coastal city offers a mix of bustling markets, modern boardwalks, and beautiful beaches. It serves as a gateway to Kinabalu National Park, home to Mount Kinabalu. The city center has a vibrant atmosphere with an old Hong Kong vibe and is famous for its seafood restaurants and night markets.
name: Kota Kinabalu
address: Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Sapi Island Jetty is a smaller but well-equipped island with amenities like bathrooms, cafes, and snorkel gear shops. The crystal-clear waters and white sandy beaches make it a lovely spot for snorkeling and hiking. While the snorkeling area may be smaller than that of Manukan Island, the friendly staff contribute to a great experience on the island.
name: Sapi Island Jetty
address: Unnamed Road,, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Bird sanctuary with trails in mangrove forest with some 80 species, including herons & kingfishers.
detail_description: The Kota Kinabalu Wetland Ramsar Site, managed by the Sabah Wetlands Conservation Society, is a 24-hectare bird sanctuary and mangrove forest with over 80 species including herons and kingfishers. It offers eco-tourism activities and educational programs to raise awareness about the importance of wetland ecosystems. Visitors can participate in environmental education programs, volunteer for mangrove clean-up, or become voluntary guardians to help manage the site.
name: Kota Kinabalu Wetland Ramsar Site
address: Jln Bukit Bendera, Upper Likas, 88400 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Kokol Hill Elf is a popular destination near Kota Kinabalu, offering a serene escape just a half-hour drive from the city. Visitors can stay at the peaceful Kokol Heights Villa and enjoy cool breezes, with the chance to catch sight of Mount Kinabalu in the morning. The hill provides stunning views of Mount Kinabalu and is an ideal spot for a romantic sunset experience. It's perfect for those seeking tranquility amidst nature away from the city's hustle and bustle.
name: Kokol Hill Elf
address: Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: KK Waterfront is the go-to destination in Kota Kinabalu for a vibrant night out. It offers an array of dining options, from local delicacies to international cuisine, as well as lively entertainment venues like pubs, karaoke bars, and a dance club. The area is conveniently located near various hotels, making it easily accessible for visitors.
name: KK Waterfront
address: Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Kota Kinabalu City Park is a must-visit destination in the city. The highlight of the park is the impressive Kota Kinabalu City Mosque, which stands on stilts above a lagoon, creating a stunning visual effect. It has a capacity for 12,000 worshippers and is one of the most beautiful buildings in the area. Additionally, visitors can explore pleasant parks like Perdana Park and learn about the city's history at war memorials.
name: Kota Kinabalu City Park
address: Jln Tun Razak, Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Aquarium focused on environmental education, featuring 1200+ marine species & hands-on exhibits.
detail_description: The Green Connection is an aquarium and ecology center in Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, dedicated to environmental education and sustainability. It houses over 1200 marine species and offers hands-on exhibits for visitors to learn about marine life worldwide. The facility hosts workshops and events for all ages, focusing on topics such as recycling, environmental conservation, and respect for nature.
name: Green Connection
address: 2, Jln Tuaran, Likas, 88450 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Gaya Street in Kota Kinabalu is renowned for its diverse dining options, making it a top destination for food enthusiasts. The area is dotted with numerous restaurants and street vendors offering a wide array of delectable street food. Despite being bustling and crowded, the vibrant atmosphere and affordable culinary delights make Gaya Street a must-visit location for those seeking an authentic gastronomic experience.
name: Gaya Street
address: Jalan Pantai, Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Embark on the North Borneo Train Tour, a nostalgic journey aboard a vintage British steam train that takes you on a four-hour round trip to Papar. The scenic ride traverses through towns and lush forests, making occasional stops along the way. Upon reaching Papar, visitors can extend their stay at the Beringgis Beach Resort and Spa for some leisurely days of swimming in both pool and ocean, indulging in local cuisine from roadside eateries.
name: North Borneo Train Tour
address: 19-1, 1st Floor, Bundusan Commercial Centre, Jalan Bundusan, Penampang, 88300 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Ikan Bilis Terbaik Sabah (Akif)13 Filipino Market is located near the Centre Point Shopping Complex on Jalan Tun Fuad Stephens. It's popularly known as the Filipino Market due to its majority of stalls being run by Filipino immigrants. The market offers an authentic and budget-friendly experience with open-air hawker food stalls serving delicious barbecued fish and chicken wings, making it a must-visit for those looking for a true taste of local cuisine in Sabah.
name: Ikan Bilis Terbaik Sabah (Akif)13 Filipino Market)
address: No 13, pasar Ikan Masin, Jln Tun Fuad Stephens, Pusat Bandar Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Partially surrounded by a lagoon, this grand mosque with a blue & gold dome offers tours.
detail_description: Masjid Bandaraya Kota Kinabalu is a grand mosque with a stunning blue and gold dome, partially surrounded by a lagoon. It offers tours and is a highlight of city tours in Kota Kinabalu. The area also includes Signal Hill, State Government Building, Double Six Monument, Atkinson Tower, Jalan Gaya, and other attractions. Additionally, visitors can enjoy the tranquility of the sea and the liveliness of the city.
name: Masjid Bandaraya Kota Kinabalu
address: Jalan Pasir, Jalan Teluk Likas, Kampung Likas, 88400 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: City park with lakeside jogging trails, kids' play areas & nightly musical fountain performances.
detail_description: Tanjung Aru Perdana Park is a popular city park in Kota Kinabalu, featuring lakeside jogging trails, kids' play areas, and nightly musical fountain performances. It's a great place to spend time with friends without spending much money. The park offers winding paths with water ponds, green spaces, and shady trees for relaxation. At night, the colorful musical fountain show adds excitement and joy to the atmosphere, making it an ideal spot for evening strolls and relaxation.
name: Tanjung Aru Perdana Park
address: Tanjung Aru, 88100 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Famed night market offering varied Southeast Asian street food cooked & sold from stalls.
detail_description: The Night Food Market in Kota Kinabalu is a renowned spot that offers a diverse range of Southeast Asian street food from various stalls. One highlight is the Filipino Night Market, located by the waterfront and known for its superb hawker stalls offering delectable seafood such as fresh oysters and massive prawns. In contrast, the Gaya Street Sunday Market provides a different experience, catering more to locals with unadvertised offerings.
name: Night Food Market
address: Jln Tun Fuad Stephens, Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Modern mall housing international restaurants, a food court, a department store & global brands.
detail_description: Suria Sabah is a modern shopping mall located in the heart of Kota Kinabalu city, offering a diverse range of international restaurants, retail outlets, and entertainment options. The mall aims to cater to visitors' needs by housing retailers with specialties ranging from daily necessities to fashion and souvenirs. Its strategic location provides stunning views of the South China Sea and Tunku Abdul Rahman National Park, as well as easy access to Jessleton Point.
name: Suria Sabah
address: 1, Jln Tun Fuad Stephens, Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: The works of local & international artists in a state gallery with unique architecture.
detail_description: The Sabah Art Gallery is a state gallery showcasing the works of both local and international artists within a uniquely designed building. Visitors can also explore museum properties, an ethnobotanical garden, a zoo, and a heritage village on the same grounds. The gallery features various exhibitions on Islamic civilization, archaeology, history, natural history, ceramics, and Brassware. Its mission is to collect and preserve ethnographic, archaeological, historical, art-historical collections throughout the state.
name: Sabah Art Gallery
address: 14, Jalan Shantung, 88300 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: The Marine Ecology Research Centre, also known as MERC, is situated on Gaya Island and offers an educational and interactive experience for visitors of all ages. The center provides guided tours for children, emphasizing the significance of reef conservation and showcasing their efforts in reef regeneration. Visitors can explore a live touch tank featuring various marine life such as starfish, corals, and giant clams. Additionally, the center educates guests about the importance of preserving marine life and advises against touching them.
name: Marine Ecology Research Centre
address: Gaya Island, Malohom Bay, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Kota Kinabalu International Airport, the second busiest airport in Malaysia, serves as a vital connection for both domestic and international flights to Sabah. Travelers can easily access the city center via an airport bus or ride-sharing services like Uber or Grab. The airport offers efficient check-in processes and comfortable seating near the gates, with clean facilities and a selection of shops to explore.
name: Kota Kinabalu International Airport
address: 134, Aras 5 邮政, 编码:, 88740 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Kiulu White Water Rafting Centre offers an unforgettable experience on the Kadamaian River, featuring Grade 1-2 rapids suitable for both beginners and seasoned rafters. The picturesque spot is located about an hour away from Kota Kinabalu city center, providing a lovely view of Mount Kinabalu and the surrounding countryside as you paddle down the river. The friendly guides ensure a safe and enjoyable adventure, with cool river waters and simple local-style lunch provided.
name: Kiulu White Water Rafting Centre
address: Jalan Tamparuli Kiulu, 89250 Tamparuli, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Unique, 30-story glass tower built in 1977, with a cylinder shape & revolving lookout floor.
detail_description: Located in Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia, the Tun Mustapha Tower, also known as the Menara Tun Mustapha or Sabah Foundation Building, is a remarkable 30-story glass tower with a unique cylindrical shape. Built in the mid-1970s, it stands out as one of the most impressive modern structures in the area. The building features a revolving lookout floor and is surrounded by 2,160 reflective glass panels.
name: Tun Mustapha Tower
address: 88400 Kota Kinabalu, Malaysia

detail_description: The Sabah Islamic Civilization Museum is a part of the Sabah State Museum and offers an immersive experience in Muslim culture, history, and heritage. The museum's Islamic World Gallery showcases a variety of artifacts such as an 18th-century Persian Quran stand, Indonesian wooden caskets with Quranic engravings, old Qurans, and miniature mosques. Visitors can explore ancient artifacts from Middle Eastern countries that illustrate the spread of Islam throughout Southeast Asia and its arrival in Sabah and Malaysia.
name: Sabah Islamic Civilization Museum
address: Jalan Menteri, Karamunsing, 88100 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Tanjung Aru is a sub-district of Kota Kinabalu in Sabah, of Malaysia. Its main feature is its beach called Tanjung Aru Beach which stretches to over 2 kilometres long along with new skyscrapers. This beach has a lot of Casuarina equisetifolia trees there naming this town. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Tanjung Aru, located in Sabah, Malaysia, is a sub-district of Kota Kinabalu known for its picturesque Tanjung Aru Beach. The beach spans over 2 kilometers and is lined with Casuarina equisetifolia trees, giving the town its name. In addition to the stunning coastline, Tanjung Aru boasts modern skyscrapers that contribute to its scenic skyline.
name: Tanjung Aru
address: 88100 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Polished villas in a beachfront resort offering a posh spa, fine dining & a dive school, plus a gym.
detail_description: Gaya Island Resort is a luxurious beachfront retreat with around one hundred polished villas nestled amidst lush jungle foliage and overlooking the sea. This 5-star resort offers an outdoor pool, yoga classes, and a pampering Spa Village. Guests can indulge in local and international cuisines at the Feast Village or savor freshly caught seafood at the rooftop Fisherman's Cove.
name: Gaya Island Resort
address: Malohom Bay Tunku Abdul Rahman, Marine Park, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Park & monument memorializing the 1976 Double Six air disaster in which Sabah's chief minister died.
detail_description: Double Six Memorial Park is a significant site in Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, commemorating the tragic 1976 Double Six air disaster that claimed the lives of Sabah's chief minister and six other ministers. The monument stands at Grace Point and serves as a poignant reminder of the devastating event. Visitors can also explore nearby attractions such as Signal Hill, Masjid Bandaraya Kota Kinabalu, and Atkinson Tower as part of a city tour.
name: Double Six Memorial Park
address: Grace Garden, 88100 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: Malaysian island featuring seaside resorts, sandy beaches & protected tropical forests.
detail_description: Gaya Island, located in the Tunku Abdul Rahman National Park in Malaysia, is a picturesque island known for its pristine rainforest and well-preserved mangroves. The island boasts several kilometers of white sandy beaches with clear waters ideal for diving and snorkeling among colorful fish and coral reefs. Accessible from Jesselton Point jetty, Gaya Island offers a peaceful retreat with luxurious overwater bungalows for those seeking a more upscale experience.
name: Gaya Island
address: Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Sabah Indoor Climbing Centre is a decent rock climbing gym located in Kota Kinabalu, Sabah. The wall and boulder section is currently in decent condition, but some areas need repairs and maintenance. The instructors, Janet and Kody are skillful, friendly and patient towards their clients.
name: Sabah Indoor Climbing Centre
address: Komples Sukan Likas, Taman Cabaran Belia, 88450 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Puh Toh Si Chinese Temple, located in the heart of Kota Kinabalu, is a popular Buddhist temple known for its traditional carvings and sculptures depicting local deities. The temple features several small shrines where visitors can seek blessings and admire the intricate details on the walls. With a serene and well-maintained environment, it offers a peaceful retreat for soul-searching and contemplation.
name: Puh Toh Si Chinese Temple
address: Lorong Kelabu, 88400 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

excerpt: This historical landmark commemorates soldiers who died defending Sabah during World War II.
detail_description: Petagas War Memorial is a significant historical site in Sabah, commemorating the brave soldiers who lost their lives during World War II. The memorial garden stands as a poignant tribute to the 176 Sabahan guerillas who were tragically executed by the Japanese army in 1944. Situated at the exact location of this heartbreaking event, the well-kept grounds feature beautiful plaques inscribed with the names of the fallen heroes.
name: Petagas War Memorial
address: No.1, Jalan Bandaran, 88675, Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, 88675, Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, 88000, Malaysia

excerpt: Simple aquarium & marine museum with fish tanks, an open-water reef exhibition & mangrove walk.
detail_description: The Aquarium and Marine Museum in Kota Kinabalu, Sabah is a world-class institution that showcases the amazing marine life found in the region. The museum has a variety of exhibits including an open-water reef exhibition, fish tanks, mangrove walks, and a theater mini. Visitors are sure to enjoy the exciting displays while learning about marine conservation at the same time.
name: Aquarium & Marine Museum, Universiti Malaysia Sabah, Kota Kinabalu, Sabah.
address: Jalan UMS, 88400 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Seng Hing Coffee Shop is a must-visit culinary gem that promises an unforgettable dining experience. Renowned for its tantalizing vermilion laksa and the beloved mee tuaran, this eatery showcases the vibrant flavors of Chinese cuisine, enhanced by the artistry of wok cooking and local ingredients like Chinese red wine. After settling into the colorful Hotel Capital, I made my way to Seng Hing to indulge in their signature dish: Tuaran Mee.
name: Seng Hing Coffee Shop
address: Lot 10, Lorong Sinsuran 2, Sinsuran Kompleks, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Welcome Seafood Restaurant is a popular eatery with multiple locations in Kota Kinabalu, including one in Inanam. With over 8,000 Google reviews, it's known for serving the freshest seafood like fish, crabs, prawns, clams, oysters, and sea snails prepared in various ways. The restaurant is always bustling with hungry customers eager to savor their delicious offerings.
name: Welcome Seafood Restaurant
address: Lot G 18, Ground Floor, Kompleks, Jalan Asia City, Asia City, 88300 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

name: Borneo Quad Biking
address: Jalan Kiulu Pukak Mantob, Kampung Mantob, 89250 Kiulu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Step into Mamasita Mexican Restaurant & Tapas Bar and you'll feel like you've been transported to a lively cantina in the heart of Mexico City. The vibrant decor, adorned with Mexican folk art and captivating wall murals, sets the stage for a festive evening filled with margaritas and tacos. On Wednesdays, Fridays, and Saturdays at 8:30pm, local musicians take the stage to entertain guests with live music.
name: Mamasita Mexican Restaurant & Tapas Bar
address: 15, Lorong Dewan, Kota Kinabalu, 88800 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Yee Fung Laksa is a renowned restaurant in Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, known for its delicious laksa and beef noodle soup. The beef broth served with flat noodles, beef slices, tripe, stomach, tendon, and more has a smooth and clear texture with a strong beefy flavor. While the laksa is not very spicy compared to typical Southeast Asian dishes, it offers a unique taste and consistency. The restaurant provides quick service in an open and airy setting.
name: Yee Fung Laksa
address: 127, Jalan Gaya, Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Woo is a trendy and stylish cafe with a unique blend of subtle flair and quirkiness. The interior features a striking W-shaped granite counter slab, an eye-catching bird cage installation adorned with neon LED strips, and large windows that bathe the space in natural light. The industrial facade is balanced by chic and comfortable vibes. The menu offers hearty breakfast and brunch options as well as delectable sweet treats.
name: Woo!
address: 21, Lorong Dewan, Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Kah Hiong Ngiu Chap is a popular noodle dish in Kota Kinabalu, Sabah. The dish features a variety of beef cuts such as beef balls, brisket, tripe, tendons, and other parts served in a rich and flavorful beef broth. The restaurant simmers the beef cutlets and daikon radish for hours with their special blend of herbs and spices to infuse the broth with delicious flavors.
name: Kah Hiong Ngiu Chap
address: 2-0-10, Lorong Taman Nosoob Jaya Phase 2, Kolam Centre, 93450 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Sin Kee Bah Kut Teh Restaurant, located in Gaya Street, is a renowned spot for lovers of Bah Kut Teh. The broth is infused with Chinese herbs and spices, creating a unique and rich flavor. The menu offers tender pork stews, lean meat, pork ribs, and pork balls that pair perfectly with the aromatic broth. Additionally, the restaurant serves delicious sides like pickled veggies and enoki mushrooms to complement the main dish.
name: Sin Kee Bah Kut Teh Restaurant
address: 26, Jalan Pantai, Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: October Coffee Gaya is a rustic cafe in Kota Kinabalu known for its high-quality coffee, cozy interiors, and delicious quick bites. The cafe offers a speciality house blend along with other bean options and provides a comfortable escape from the city with its wooden fixtures and greenery. Additionally, it features sweet and savory bites on the menu including scones, beef bruschetta, and freshly baked cakes.
name: October Coffee Gaya
address: 13, Lorong Dewan, Pusat Bandar, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: Anjung Kinabalu, also known as KK Night Market, is a bustling paradise for seafood enthusiasts that operates daily from around 4.30 pm at the parking lot in front of the Central Market. It offers an immersive experience where visitors can select fresh seafood from the Wet Market, haggle over prices, and choose their preferred cooking method.
name: Anjung Kinabalu (AKINA Night Market)
address: Jln Tun Fuad Stephens, Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

detail_description: The Yen Ai cafe is a great spot for authentic Chinese herbal tea and desserts. Families frequent the establishment most of the time, so it's always crowded. The menu offers a variety of choices for herbal tea and sweets, with prices starting to get expensive after recent renovations. The soup here is delicious, with a robust flavor that dominates over the sweetness of the beans. Try the tang yuan (a type of spring roll) during festive season!
name: Yen Ai
address: Ground Floor Lot 6, Bornion Centre, Luyang Commercial Centre, 88300 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia

name: Water Village
address: Pusat Bandar Kota Kinabalu, 88000 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia
